title: Private/Tribal High Value
name: Private/Tribal High Value
description:
Private lands voluntarily managed to protect wildlife and restore ecosystems.  These include working ranches under ecologically oriented management.  Biologically important areas in the Wildlands Network are mapped
without regard to ownership for SITES and focal species.  If important areas fall on private or tribal lands, then of course those owners make the decisions as to how the land is managed.  However, we hope to alert them to the conservation value of their lands, and it may be worthwhile for all parties to explore options for cooperation.
